  "text": "Finally, note that conditional disclosure of secrets (CDS) is often used as a tool to one step beyond linear operations. For example, it is possible to securely evaluate greater than predicate using CDS protocols [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . As somewhat fully homomorphic encryption (SFE) remains additively homomoprhic even if we have exhausted all multiplication operations, it is possible to combine CDS with SFE to extend the set of functions computable with SHE without extending itsmultiplicative depth.",
